00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:00:41,898 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:46,278 --> 00:00:48,737
ANNALS OF THE JOSEON DYNASTY
ANJONG, YEAR 6, VOLUME 12, MAY 23

3
00:00:48,820 --> 00:00:53,408
A STAR WITH A RED TAIL APPEARED
AND DID NOT VANISH FOR TWO MONTHS

4
00:00:53,492 --> 00:00:55,327
FAMINE AND PLAGUE BROKE OUT
ACROSS THE NATION

5
00:00:55,410 --> 00:00:57,496
THIS WAS WHEN LADY KANG
A MERE CONCUBINE

6
00:00:57,579 --> 00:00:59,373
WAS APPOINTED TO THE RANK OF BIN

7
00:01:04,836 --> 00:01:07,214
TO PREVENT DISASTER
AND HEED HEAVEN'S WARNING

8
00:01:07,297 --> 00:01:09,466
PETITIONS FROM THE MINISTERS POURED IN

9
00:01:23,586 --> 00:01:26,656
INJEONGMUN GATE

10
00:01:27,442 --> 00:01:30,362
"By royal edict, the order given
shall now be carried out."

11
00:01:31,196 --> 00:01:33,448
"Royal Consort Hui of the Kang clan,
of the Inner Court,

12
00:01:33,532 --> 00:01:35,617
has committed a heinous crime."

13
00:01:35,701 --> 00:01:37,786
"The crime of disrupting
the Inner Court's hierarchy."

14
00:01:37,869 --> 00:01:39,413
"The crime of adultery."

15
00:01:39,496 --> 00:01:42,749
"And the attempted assassination of
the Firstborn Prince and Consort Gyeong."

16
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:44,918
"Thus, Royal Consort Hui is
hereby sentenced to death by poison

17
00:01:45,001 --> 00:01:47,963
to set right the Crown and the state."

18
00:01:49,798 --> 00:01:52,968
Royal Consort Hui shall come forth
and receive the royal command!

19
00:02:04,146 --> 00:02:07,816
Your Highness, you must go outside.

20
00:02:09,359 --> 00:02:10,444
You need not hasten me.

21
00:02:14,614 --> 00:02:15,949
It is finished.

22
00:02:24,499 --> 00:02:27,085
Plum blossoms in bloom
amidst the bitter snow of winter.

23
00:02:29,296 --> 00:02:31,339
Are they not captivating?

24
00:02:33,216 --> 00:02:35,886
Flowers that blossom
on a gentle spring day are never…

25
00:02:39,181 --> 00:02:40,599
sufficient to content the heart.

26
00:02:40,682 --> 00:02:42,517
-Your Highness.
-Your Highness.

27
00:02:42,601 --> 00:02:43,977
Your Highness.

28
00:02:49,691 --> 00:02:50,984
Let us go.

29
00:03:30,982 --> 00:03:33,360
Have you gathered
to revel in this spectacle?

30
00:03:33,443 --> 00:03:35,111
At the mere rumor of my death…

31
00:03:38,031 --> 00:03:39,616
those who would dance upon my grave

32
00:03:40,951 --> 00:03:42,911
come swarming like ravenous hounds.

33
00:03:44,246 --> 00:03:48,250
They say no blossom endures
its bloom forever.

34
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:06,393
BUREAU OF SHAMANIC RITUALS

35
00:04:13,191 --> 00:04:19,823
HYANGSEON HALL

36
00:04:48,059 --> 00:04:49,811
<i>It ought to have been delivered by now.</i>

37
00:04:49,895 --> 00:04:51,062
Yes.

38
00:04:51,146 --> 00:04:54,274
It is past noon, so the royal edict
must have been delivered, Your Majesty.

39
00:04:54,357 --> 00:04:58,028
The rot has been cut away.
No need to sever the limb now.

40
00:04:58,111 --> 00:04:59,654
However, Your Majesty,

41
00:04:59,738 --> 00:05:02,616
amid the famine wrought by drought
and the advent of that ill-omened star,

42
00:05:02,699 --> 00:05:04,951
the people grow restless.

43
00:05:05,035 --> 00:05:09,164
You must swiftly root out the remnants
who followed Lady Kang.

44
00:05:09,247 --> 00:05:11,333
Minister, do you seek
a bloodbath the like of that

45
00:05:11,416 --> 00:05:12,834
which befell in the Year of Gihae?

46
00:05:12,918 --> 00:05:14,753
Let the ministers speak

47
00:05:16,046 --> 00:05:18,131
of this matter no more.

48
00:05:23,219 --> 00:05:24,679
Go in peace.

49
00:05:26,681 --> 00:05:27,807
<i>You will not see me depart.</i>

50
00:05:29,309 --> 00:05:31,186
Did you think
I would acquiesce in silence?

51
00:05:33,772 --> 00:05:34,689
How dare you!

52
00:05:34,773 --> 00:05:36,983
Pray tell, what precisely is my crime?

53
00:05:37,067 --> 00:05:39,235
Restoring order
to the Inner Court's hierarchy?

54
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:42,530
Daring to stand above the daughters
of noble families despite my low birth?

55
00:05:42,614 --> 00:05:43,531
Or is it…

56
00:05:45,116 --> 00:05:48,453
that I contended for my life
in this treacherous palace,

57
00:05:50,121 --> 00:05:52,666
where all conspired against it?

58
00:05:55,210 --> 00:05:56,419
If that be a crime…

59
00:05:58,546 --> 00:06:01,091
then you all stand guilty of the same sin!

60
00:06:01,174 --> 00:06:02,050
Such insolence!

61
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:05,595
How dare you cast aside the poison
bestowed by royal command!

62
00:06:05,679 --> 00:06:07,097
Go and tell His Majesty

63
00:06:07,931 --> 00:06:10,266
that this rusted blade
yet has words for him.

64
00:06:11,559 --> 00:06:12,644
Until then…

65
00:06:15,146 --> 00:06:17,065
I shall not so much as take a single sip.

66
00:06:17,148 --> 00:06:18,650
Hear me. Bring forth the poison.

67
00:06:36,167 --> 00:06:37,669
How dare you!

68
00:06:40,463 --> 00:06:41,715
Why you…

69
00:06:47,053 --> 00:06:48,221
Make her drink.

70
00:06:57,814 --> 00:06:58,773
Let go!

71
00:07:00,025 --> 00:07:02,110
How dare you lay
your filthy hands upon me!

72
00:07:03,653 --> 00:07:04,612
Let go!

73
00:07:06,781 --> 00:07:08,074
Let go!

74
00:07:26,885 --> 00:07:28,970
Shamaness, are you all right?

75
00:07:29,054 --> 00:07:30,263
What should we do?

76
00:07:30,346 --> 00:07:31,931
It is raining! Rain is falling!

77
00:07:35,602 --> 00:07:36,644
Your Highness.

78
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:41,232
My powers are weak.
This was the only way.

79
00:07:43,359 --> 00:07:45,361
I humbly pray for your health and peace.

80
00:07:57,373 --> 00:08:00,168
Even the heavens take heed,
now that the wicked vixen is gone.

81
00:08:00,251 --> 00:08:03,296
The rain we prayed for has finally come.

82
00:08:03,379 --> 00:08:05,632
Wait, this is frost, not rain.

83
00:08:06,132 --> 00:08:08,301
What? Frost in the middle of summer?

84
00:08:21,439 --> 00:08:22,774
What is that?

85
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:38,915
The sun…

86
00:08:41,918 --> 00:08:43,253
What is going on?

87
00:08:43,336 --> 00:08:44,921
The sun just disappeared.

88
00:09:14,033 --> 00:09:15,076
<i>Is this how…</i>

89
00:09:19,122 --> 00:09:20,498
<i>I depart this world?</i>

90
00:09:24,627 --> 00:09:25,879
<i>Perhaps…</i>

91
00:09:28,006 --> 00:09:29,340
<i>this is my…</i>

92
00:10:04,709 --> 00:10:07,921
Royal Consort Hui of the Jang clan
shall drink the poison!

93
00:10:20,934 --> 00:10:22,060
<i>Am I…</i>

94
00:10:23,519 --> 00:10:24,812
<i>not dead yet?</i>

95
00:10:27,398 --> 00:10:28,316
My goodness.

96
00:10:29,192 --> 00:10:31,527
<i>I must have lost my senses for a moment.</i>

97
00:10:37,784 --> 00:10:39,535
<i>Why is the sun so close?</i>

98
00:10:41,746 --> 00:10:43,623
<i>How much of that poison did I drink?</i>

99
00:10:44,540 --> 00:10:45,875
<i>I keep seeing things.</i>

100
00:10:51,464 --> 00:10:53,508
<i>What are all those people doing?</i>

101
00:10:54,050 --> 00:10:56,219
Cut! That was great. Really great.

102
00:10:56,844 --> 00:10:58,263
Let's turn it around.

103
00:10:58,346 --> 00:10:59,713
What’s next?

104
00:11:02,183 --> 00:11:04,224
-Props, we're resetting.
-Director, about our next scene…

105
00:11:04,324 --> 00:11:05,478
It's scene 18.

106
00:11:05,561 --> 00:11:07,438
-Full shot first.
-Yes, sir.

107
00:11:07,522 --> 00:11:08,731
Full shot first.

108
00:11:08,815 --> 00:11:10,066
Was the audio okay?

109
00:11:13,528 --> 00:11:15,363
CHWISEONDANG HALL

110
00:11:17,740 --> 00:11:20,118
Wow, that stand-in is really great.

111
00:11:20,201 --> 00:11:22,287
She did the death so believably.
It wasn't even meant to be that dramatic.

112
00:11:22,370 --> 00:11:25,164
Did Ji-hyo really need
a stand-in for this scene?

113
00:11:25,248 --> 00:11:27,667
She said she's allergic to
the herbal medicine used for the poison.

114
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:30,086
-What can we do?
-Jeez.

115
00:11:30,169 --> 00:11:31,421
That's good.

116
00:11:31,504 --> 00:11:33,881
All right, let's go again. Right away.

117
00:11:33,965 --> 00:11:35,800
<i>What is going on here?</i>

118
00:11:36,551 --> 00:11:38,511
<i>The way those people are dressed…</i>

119
00:11:39,345 --> 00:11:41,556
<i>They do not even wear</i>
<i>their hair in topknots.</i>

120
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:47,937
<i>In broad daylight, that woman</i>

121
00:11:48,021 --> 00:11:49,856
<i>so wantonly lays bare her limbs.</i>

122
00:11:49,939 --> 00:11:51,357
Such insolence.

123
00:11:51,441 --> 00:11:52,567
Here we go.

124
00:11:53,735 --> 00:11:55,528
Okay, let's go again. Right now.

125
00:11:55,611 --> 00:11:58,364
-Ready? Let's go.
-Okay, roll sound.

126
00:11:58,448 --> 00:12:00,533
Camera, go!

127
00:12:00,616 --> 00:12:02,035
Ready, action!

128
00:12:03,369 --> 00:12:05,913
Royal Consort Hui of the Jang clan
shall drink the poison!

129
00:12:05,997 --> 00:12:06,998
Jang clan?

130
00:12:07,081 --> 00:12:09,417
And now you err even in my family name?

131
00:12:10,168 --> 00:12:11,627
I am of the Kang clan!

132
00:12:14,422 --> 00:12:15,840
Hey, keep it rolling.

133
00:12:18,634 --> 00:12:22,180
I knew a wench like you
would not submit in peace.

134
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:26,059
Guards! Pour the poison
down this wench's throat!

135
00:12:26,142 --> 00:12:27,727
A wench, you say?

136
00:12:27,810 --> 00:12:29,771
They ought to tear you limb from limb!

137
00:12:31,189 --> 00:12:32,690
Is Shin Seo-ri crazy?

138
00:12:32,774 --> 00:12:35,151
Look at her improvising
when she's supposed to be my stand-in.

139
00:12:35,234 --> 00:12:37,320
-Who does she think she is?
-I know, right?

140
00:12:37,403 --> 00:12:38,780
Isn't she just an extra?

141
00:12:44,952 --> 00:12:47,830
Seize! Seize that wench at once!

142
00:12:47,914 --> 00:12:49,832
You must not value your own neck.

143
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:51,793
You, a mere officer,

144
00:12:51,876 --> 00:12:55,213
dare to run your vile mouth
before a Senior First Rank Royal Consort!

145
00:12:55,296 --> 00:12:56,964
Seize her!

146
00:13:01,552 --> 00:13:02,929
Stand back, you scoundrels!

147
00:13:03,429 --> 00:13:05,223
Before I have your filthy hands cut off.

148
00:13:05,306 --> 00:13:08,476
Seize her! Make her drink the poison!

149
00:13:09,936 --> 00:13:11,229
Damn it.

150
00:13:17,443 --> 00:13:18,403
Damn you!

151
00:13:29,956 --> 00:13:32,458
All of you, get her!

152
00:13:32,542 --> 00:13:34,168
-Get her!
-Get her!

153
00:13:39,966 --> 00:13:41,634
How is she so strong?

154
00:13:50,810 --> 00:13:54,063
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

155
00:13:54,147 --> 00:13:57,275
EPISODE 1
THE VIXEN AND THE BEAST

156
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,986
<i>A video showing</i>
<i>CEO Cha Se-gye abusing his power</i>

157
00:14:00,069 --> 00:14:01,779
<i>was released this morning, branding him</i>

158
00:14:01,863 --> 00:14:04,699
<i>the worst third-generation</i>
<i>chaebol heir in the nation's history</i>

159
00:14:04,782 --> 00:14:07,493
<i>and fueling debate</i>
<i>over corporate succession.</i>

160
00:14:07,577 --> 00:14:10,621
<i>Mr. Cha Se-gye, the grandson</i>
<i>of Chail Group founder Cha Dal-su,</i>

161
00:14:10,705 --> 00:14:13,166
<i>who now runs startup Biojei</i>
<i>after resigning from the group,</i>

162
00:14:13,249 --> 00:14:14,876
<i>is mired in another abuse</i>
<i>of power scandal.</i>

163
00:14:14,959 --> 00:14:15,960
There he is!

164
00:14:29,223 --> 00:14:31,309
<i>A ruthless M&amp;A butcher.</i>

165
00:14:35,229 --> 00:14:37,815
<i>That's what everyone calls Cha Se-gye.</i>

166
00:14:37,899 --> 00:14:41,068
<i>A savage abandoned</i>
<i>by the business world.</i>

167
00:14:41,152 --> 00:14:45,156
<i>A vampire, a money-grubber,</i>
<i>a monster of capitalism.</i>

168
00:14:45,239 --> 00:14:48,826
<i>I understand it's your company's custom</i>
<i>to never dismiss a single employee.</i>

169
00:14:48,910 --> 00:14:50,161
<i>So, convince me.</i>

170
00:14:50,244 --> 00:14:52,163
Why should I bother
to protect that damn tradition

171
00:14:52,246 --> 00:14:54,832
when I could just sell the company off,
shredding it piece by piece?

172
00:14:54,916 --> 00:14:56,918
This differs
from the agreed acquisition terms.

173
00:14:57,001 --> 00:15:00,588
If you're going to change
your tune like this, I can't sign.

174
00:15:01,797 --> 00:15:03,007
You're going to have to.

175
00:15:04,884 --> 00:15:07,011
This is your first and last chance

176
00:15:07,094 --> 00:15:10,139
to get even a pittance
for that measly company of yours.

177
00:15:13,559 --> 00:15:14,644
Oh right.

178
00:15:16,354 --> 00:15:18,147
If you intend to secure FDA approval

179
00:15:18,231 --> 00:15:20,733
for your cosmetic ingredient
as a pharmaceutical-grade product

180
00:15:20,816 --> 00:15:23,486
to inflate its value,
you can just forget it.

181
00:15:24,028 --> 00:15:25,530
But that's confidential information--

182
00:15:25,613 --> 00:15:28,491
My very capable lobbyists
are always working hard.

183
00:15:28,991 --> 00:15:31,410
It's going to be rejected
due to safety concerns.

184
00:15:31,994 --> 00:15:32,995
Mr. Cha.

185
00:15:33,079 --> 00:15:35,998
Let's just call this deal off. All right?

186
00:15:37,959 --> 00:15:40,378
I figured you'd do that,
so I brought an extra.

187
00:15:40,461 --> 00:15:43,172
Mr. Cha, what the hell
do you think you're doing?

188
00:15:43,256 --> 00:15:45,424
I'm giving you a choice.

189
00:15:45,508 --> 00:15:48,010
Either go bankrupt from rumors
of your material's side effects,

190
00:15:48,094 --> 00:15:50,096
or restructure, hand over the company,

191
00:15:50,179 --> 00:15:52,265
and at least walk away with your shares.

192
00:15:52,348 --> 00:15:55,101
Now, the price drops
by a billion won every ten seconds.

193
00:15:59,188 --> 00:16:01,023
You can't be serious.

194
00:16:02,608 --> 00:16:04,277
You just lost a billion won.

195
00:16:05,486 --> 00:16:06,946
PURCHASE PRICE: KRW 5,620,400,000

196
00:16:07,029 --> 00:16:08,614
All right, two billion is next.

197
00:16:14,245 --> 00:16:17,873
This isn't some flea market
where you can just haggle.

198
00:16:17,957 --> 00:16:19,041
What kind of negotiation--

199
00:16:19,125 --> 00:16:20,918
And you've lost three billion.

200
00:16:21,002 --> 00:16:22,295
PURCHASE PRICE: KRW 3,620,400,000

201
00:16:22,378 --> 00:16:25,423
What will it be? Do you need more time?

202
00:16:28,217 --> 00:16:30,761
No. I'll sign.

203
00:16:44,734 --> 00:16:45,901
Took you long enough.

204
00:16:45,985 --> 00:16:47,903
You just threw away three billion won.

205
00:16:58,831 --> 00:17:01,667
<i>Hello, this is Handy, your friend at noon.</i>

206
00:17:01,751 --> 00:17:04,754
<i>I'm sure you've all heard</i>
<i>about the once-in-300-years eclipse.</i>

207
00:17:04,837 --> 00:17:07,256
<i>They say our ancestors called</i>
<i>an eclipse a natural disaster.</i>

208
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:09,759
Maybe a natural disaster
would get me a day off.

209
00:17:09,842 --> 00:17:12,011
<i>This eclipse is special</i>
<i>because it's a collab</i>

210
00:17:12,094 --> 00:17:13,846
<i>with a comet that returns every 300 years.</i>

211
00:17:13,929 --> 00:17:16,599
<i>We'll be able to see the comet</i>
<i>with our own eyes!</i>

212
00:17:17,224 --> 00:17:19,977
<i>This afternoon's cosmic show,</i>
<i>300 years in the making.</i>

213
00:17:20,061 --> 00:17:22,855
<i>-Don't miss it.</i>
-It'd take an alien invasion

214
00:17:24,023 --> 00:17:25,191
to get a day off.

215
00:17:28,110 --> 00:17:29,904
Sir, did you enjoy your meal?

216
00:17:29,987 --> 00:17:31,322
Of course I did.

217
00:17:31,405 --> 00:17:33,949
Getting revenge on that bastard
made it all the more satisfying.

218
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:36,952
You could've gone easier on the CEO.
He came out crying.

219
00:17:38,079 --> 00:17:40,665
Mr. Son, those were all crocodile tears.

220
00:17:40,748 --> 00:17:42,500
Do you know
how many subcontractors went under

221
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:44,001
after he swapped in cheap materials?

222
00:17:44,085 --> 00:17:47,213
When I think of the three billion won
he cost me back in the day…

223
00:17:47,296 --> 00:17:49,507
I should've stripped him clean.
Damn it.

224
00:17:49,590 --> 00:17:52,802
But when he realizes he got ripped off,
it should sting a little.

225
00:17:53,886 --> 00:17:56,555
And so your infamous reputation
gets renewed once more.

226
00:17:57,765 --> 00:17:59,016
So what if I'm infamous?

227
00:17:59,725 --> 00:18:02,395
Being infamous is
the best bodyguard there is.

228
00:18:06,148 --> 00:18:07,650
Taking ten, everyone!

229
00:18:09,777 --> 00:18:11,153
Are you okay? Can we keep shooting?

230
00:18:11,237 --> 00:18:14,865
I am fine. Now, seize that man at once!

231
00:18:18,202 --> 00:18:21,956
How dare you insolent fools
defy my command?

232
00:18:25,042 --> 00:18:26,544
Hey! What's gotten into you?

233
00:18:26,627 --> 00:18:28,379
Even if you're mad at Yoon Ji-hyo,

234
00:18:28,462 --> 00:18:30,923
you can't just recklessly cause
a scene like this.

235
00:18:31,006 --> 00:18:32,049
You insolent wench.

236
00:18:32,133 --> 00:18:33,634
What? "Wench"?

237
00:18:33,718 --> 00:18:35,803
You dare raise your voice
before your superior?

238
00:18:35,886 --> 00:18:39,265
You did mention you were feeling chills.
Have you actually lost your mind?

239
00:18:39,348 --> 00:18:40,641
You're burning up!

240
00:18:40,725 --> 00:18:42,476
Okay, this is serious.

241
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:44,270
That wench, to the very end…

242
00:18:44,353 --> 00:18:46,397
Guards! Seize that wench at once…

243
00:18:47,398 --> 00:18:48,691
<i>This place…</i>

244
00:18:51,736 --> 00:18:54,280
<i>Where in the world am I?</i>

245
00:18:54,947 --> 00:18:56,866
<i>The way these people are dressed…</i>

246
00:18:57,366 --> 00:18:58,743
It was so heavy earlier.

247
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:03,330
<i>The women wear no head coverings</i>
<i>and converse with men outside their kin.</i>

248
00:19:08,169 --> 00:19:09,295
Yellow hair?

249
00:19:09,837 --> 00:19:12,631
<i>Yellow hair and blue eyes?</i>

250
00:19:12,715 --> 00:19:15,092
<i>Could that be a Westerner from the tales?</i>

251
00:19:15,176 --> 00:19:18,721
Westerners are roaming
the palace in a horde.

252
00:19:19,263 --> 00:19:22,057
Did I end up in a foreign land
while I was unconscious?

253
00:19:22,850 --> 00:19:26,896
Excuse me.
Your performance was incredible.

254
00:19:28,898 --> 00:19:31,859
You can speak the Joseon tongue?

255
00:19:31,942 --> 00:19:33,110
Joseon?

256
00:19:33,194 --> 00:19:34,779
You mean Korean?

257
00:19:34,862 --> 00:19:36,197
Yes, a little.

258
00:19:37,156 --> 00:19:38,991
A picture together, okay?

259
00:19:48,584 --> 00:19:51,504
What… in the world is this?

260
00:19:51,587 --> 00:19:54,465
My face. Why does it look like that?

261
00:19:54,548 --> 00:19:56,425
This looking glass is strange.

262
00:20:16,737 --> 00:20:18,239
What are you doing?

263
00:20:18,823 --> 00:20:20,032
Shin Seo-ri, are you nuts?

264
00:20:20,115 --> 00:20:21,492
My face…

265
00:20:22,618 --> 00:20:23,828
I've aged so horribly.

266
00:20:24,453 --> 00:20:25,871
What are you saying? Hey!

267
00:20:25,955 --> 00:20:27,581
Hey! Give me my mirror back!

268
00:20:27,665 --> 00:20:29,124
You worthless bastards!

269
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:31,293
Must I waste my time

270
00:20:31,919 --> 00:20:32,878
because

271
00:20:33,462 --> 00:20:34,713
of bastards

272
00:20:35,589 --> 00:20:37,091
like you? Damn it!

273
00:20:40,135 --> 00:20:41,345
What the…

274
00:20:41,428 --> 00:20:43,430
-Mr. Son.
-Yes, sir.

275
00:20:45,224 --> 00:20:46,141
Is this me?

276
00:20:47,434 --> 00:20:49,854
It's a deepfake video. Seamless, isn't it?

277
00:20:52,773 --> 00:20:54,692
So my face was maliciously edited

278
00:20:54,775 --> 00:20:56,235
to be posted all over the internet,

279
00:20:56,318 --> 00:20:57,778
and I had no idea?

280
00:20:58,404 --> 00:20:59,405
Don't worry, sir.

281
00:20:59,488 --> 00:21:01,115
Our legal team filed a lawsuit.

282
00:21:01,198 --> 00:21:02,616
The PR team also released a statement

283
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,118
condemning the malicious deepfake.

284
00:21:04,201 --> 00:21:06,620
No, Mr. Son. What are you talking about?

285
00:21:06,704 --> 00:21:09,707
We should be rewarding them,
not punishing them.

286
00:21:09,790 --> 00:21:10,749
Pardon?

287
00:21:10,833 --> 00:21:14,461
Domestic tech has gotten so good
that even I was fooled.

288
00:21:14,545 --> 00:21:17,298
Is this really the time
to be filing lawsuits?

289
00:21:18,132 --> 00:21:20,759
Get the legal team on the phone now

290
00:21:20,843 --> 00:21:22,386
and set up a meeting with them.

291
00:21:22,469 --> 00:21:24,597
I'm going to acquire this company too.

292
00:21:26,098 --> 00:21:27,308
Understood, sir.

293
00:21:27,850 --> 00:21:29,935
This really is amazing.

294
00:21:35,608 --> 00:21:39,153
<i>What in the world has befallen me?</i>

295
00:21:40,863 --> 00:21:41,780
<i>My blood?</i>

296
00:21:41,864 --> 00:21:44,658
What purpose do you have for my blood?

297
00:21:44,742 --> 00:21:47,786
Your Highness must die in order to live.

298
00:21:47,870 --> 00:21:50,581
If I wish to live,
I must offer you my blood?

299
00:22:00,174 --> 00:22:01,675
<i>The cut has disappeared.</i>

300
00:22:02,426 --> 00:22:04,887
<i>Hwang most certainly drew my blood.</i>

301
00:22:05,512 --> 00:22:08,140
<i>There is no way</i>
<i>it could have healed overnight.</i>

302
00:22:09,099 --> 00:22:10,643
<i>Which means…</i>

303
00:22:11,518 --> 00:22:12,436
<i>That cannot be.</i>

304
00:22:13,812 --> 00:22:15,940
<i>Have I been placed in another body?</i>

305
00:22:16,982 --> 00:22:19,985
<i>Your Highness must die in order to live.</i>

306
00:22:20,069 --> 00:22:22,237
So when she said I must die to live…

307
00:22:23,656 --> 00:22:24,698
This is what she meant?

308
00:22:31,622 --> 00:22:33,248
"After changing his clothes,
Prince Edward…

309
00:22:33,321 --> 00:22:35,000
2026 CHAIL E&amp;C
CHILD SPONSORSHIP EVENT

310
00:22:35,084 --> 00:22:37,086
…put on the crown
and became the new king."

311
00:22:37,169 --> 00:22:40,089
"Tom the pauper was rewarded handsomely

312
00:22:40,172 --> 00:22:41,298
for all his help."

313
00:22:41,382 --> 00:22:44,718
"And Edward became a great king

314
00:22:44,802 --> 00:22:46,637
in the end."

315
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:48,806
His looks, his character…

316
00:22:48,889 --> 00:22:51,642
He is the very embodiment
of noblesse oblige.

317
00:22:51,725 --> 00:22:53,143
Exactly.

318
00:22:53,769 --> 00:22:56,230
Our team is doing a special feature titled

319
00:22:56,313 --> 00:22:58,315
"The State of Korea's Chaebol Heirs."

320
00:22:58,399 --> 00:23:01,735
We'll also be covering the massive layoffs
from four years ago that caused

321
00:23:01,819 --> 00:23:05,280
Chail Group's stock to plummet.

322
00:23:05,364 --> 00:23:06,740
Care to comment?

323
00:23:06,824 --> 00:23:09,743
The video hasn't been verified,
so I have no comment.

324
00:23:10,285 --> 00:23:11,745
But I can tell you this.

325
00:23:11,829 --> 00:23:15,082
Se-gye has a strong sense
of responsibility.

326
00:23:15,165 --> 00:23:18,419
I consider his swift resignation
four years ago to be indicative

327
00:23:18,502 --> 00:23:19,837
of his management skills.

328
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:22,131
It's also the secret
to Se-gye's successful startup.

329
00:23:22,214 --> 00:23:25,050
There are rumors about his mother,
'90s star Han Hye-seon,

330
00:23:25,134 --> 00:23:28,804
and his humble beginnings.
Some even call him a "half-breed chaebol."

331
00:23:28,887 --> 00:23:29,888
Sir.

332
00:23:30,597 --> 00:23:32,141
Perhaps I wasn't your first choice?

333
00:23:32,224 --> 00:23:33,684
Pardon?

334
00:23:36,020 --> 00:23:37,354
I just feel like an alternate.

335
00:23:37,438 --> 00:23:39,690
Not at all. I'm honored
to be interviewing someone

336
00:23:39,773 --> 00:23:41,734
so well respected for his kind leadership.

337
00:23:41,817 --> 00:23:43,235
That was a joke.

338
00:23:44,319 --> 00:23:46,572
-Please continue.
-Sure.

339
00:23:48,282 --> 00:23:50,951
Was Hwang always this powerful?

340
00:23:51,577 --> 00:23:53,328
What in the world is going on?

341
00:23:57,583 --> 00:23:58,459
Hey, you brat!

342
00:23:58,542 --> 00:24:01,211
Ms. Hong is furious right now.
She's ready to tear you apart!

343
00:24:01,295 --> 00:24:04,256
Such insolence!
How dare you speak to me that way?

344
00:24:07,009 --> 00:24:10,721
<i>No, I should just keep quiet</i>
<i>and observe the situation for now.</i>

345
00:24:10,804 --> 00:24:11,722
Why'd you stop?

346
00:24:11,805 --> 00:24:15,559
Then again, you must also be
embarrassed by your own behavior.

347
00:24:15,642 --> 00:24:17,144
You just threw someone down
out of nowhere.

348
00:24:17,227 --> 00:24:19,563
Then you terrorized Yoon Ji-hyo.

349
00:24:19,646 --> 00:24:21,356
I seriously thought you were possessed.

350
00:24:22,483 --> 00:24:23,859
Possessed?

351
00:24:26,195 --> 00:24:27,696
I fear my spirits ran high today,

352
00:24:27,780 --> 00:24:30,324
leading me to make a slight misstep.

353
00:24:30,407 --> 00:24:31,867
Pay it no mind.

354
00:24:32,659 --> 00:24:34,536
Hold on. Seo-ri, you've been talking

355
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:36,789
really strangely since earlier.

356
00:24:36,872 --> 00:24:38,707
You keep talking like you're from Joseon.

357
00:24:38,791 --> 00:24:39,750
Whatever do you mean?

358
00:24:39,833 --> 00:24:42,377
I am from Joseon, so I speak like one…

359
00:24:42,461 --> 00:24:43,337
<i>No.</i>

360
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:46,048
<i>Her speaking our tongue does not guarantee</i>

361
00:24:46,131 --> 00:24:47,716
<i>she is from Joseon.</i>

362
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,301
Judging by your attire,

363
00:24:49,384 --> 00:24:52,262
you seem to be a palace maid or servant.
Whom do you serve?

364
00:24:52,346 --> 00:24:54,848
-Are you from the Qing dynasty?
-What? The Qing?

365
00:24:54,932 --> 00:24:55,808
Somewhere farther?

366
00:24:55,891 --> 00:24:59,853
Then again, with all these Westerners
swarming about like dogs…

367
00:25:01,730 --> 00:25:02,815
Perhaps, Cheonchuk?

368
00:25:02,898 --> 00:25:04,691
Cheon…

369
00:25:04,775 --> 00:25:07,111
Do not tell me it is Daesik.

370
00:25:07,903 --> 00:25:09,947
What are you talking about?

371
00:25:10,572 --> 00:25:12,616
-What's wrong with you?
-Shin Seo-ri!

372
00:25:14,076 --> 00:25:15,077
Hey.

373
00:25:16,203 --> 00:25:17,371
You…

374
00:25:27,089 --> 00:25:30,342
<i>And who are these two</i>
<i>with faces like vipers?</i>

375
00:25:31,552 --> 00:25:34,304
I just ran out of a meeting
with the production company over you.

376
00:25:34,388 --> 00:25:35,514
What is wrong with you?

377
00:25:35,597 --> 00:25:36,682
<i>Just look at this creature.</i>

378
00:25:36,765 --> 00:25:40,644
<i>Her face is just plastered</i>
<i>with pure spite.</i>

379
00:25:40,727 --> 00:25:43,313
<i>Judging by her facial features,</i>

380
00:25:43,397 --> 00:25:45,399
<i>she is a wench who lives to dominate.</i>

381
00:25:45,482 --> 00:25:46,525
<i>In that case…</i>

382
00:25:46,608 --> 00:25:47,943
…and you're here chatting away?

383
00:25:48,026 --> 00:25:50,362
My situation is far from calm,

384
00:25:50,445 --> 00:25:52,281
but I am glad it appeared so to you.

385
00:25:54,491 --> 00:25:57,661
"Glad it appeared so"?

386
00:25:57,744 --> 00:25:59,913
I don't like
that tone you're using at all.

387
00:25:59,997 --> 00:26:01,915
Just because your contract
is terminated, you think

388
00:26:01,999 --> 00:26:03,667
you've nothing left to lose? Is that it?

389
00:26:03,750 --> 00:26:05,169
Ms. Hong, please calm down.

390
00:26:05,252 --> 00:26:08,255
I told you she's been acting strange.

391
00:26:08,338 --> 00:26:09,798
And who are you, wench?

392
00:26:09,882 --> 00:26:11,383
"Wench"?

393
00:26:12,217 --> 00:26:15,429
Look, I know you're angry and all,
but this is too much.

394
00:26:15,512 --> 00:26:16,722
Dismissive, now even cursing?

395
00:26:16,805 --> 00:26:18,557
Are you so pissed you've lost your mind?

396
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:19,892
<i>-I see now.</i>
-Someone else's booth…

397
00:26:19,975 --> 00:26:22,519
<i>Look at her,</i>
<i>smugly playing the peacemaker.</i>

398
00:26:22,603 --> 00:26:24,521
I see…

399
00:26:25,105 --> 00:26:29,193
Did your pride take a blow
being my stand-in?

400
00:26:29,276 --> 00:26:31,111
Because you were once
the "Nation's Pebble"?

401
00:26:31,195 --> 00:26:35,073
<i>This wench has a gift for veiled insults.</i>

402
00:26:35,157 --> 00:26:36,867
<i>And that's my specialty.</i>

403
00:26:36,950 --> 00:26:39,745
I see. So this was you.

404
00:26:39,828 --> 00:26:42,122
Such <i>unremarkable</i> features.

405
00:26:42,206 --> 00:26:44,708
I failed to recognize you at first glance.

406
00:26:52,716 --> 00:26:54,468
Maybe… you…

407
00:26:54,551 --> 00:26:57,638
Maybe you should watch what you say?

408
00:26:58,138 --> 00:27:00,224
Shin Seo-ri, you owe me a proper apology.

409
00:27:00,307 --> 00:27:02,976
<i>Seeing how worked up this wench is,</i>

410
00:27:03,060 --> 00:27:05,103
<i>it appears I have won this round.</i>

411
00:27:05,187 --> 00:27:07,606
I cannot apologize
for something I did not do.

412
00:27:07,689 --> 00:27:11,109
So instead of swarming in
and threshing me down to a husk,

413
00:27:11,193 --> 00:27:13,820
perhaps you should mind your trap first.

414
00:27:16,323 --> 00:27:17,491
Let us go.

415
00:27:25,832 --> 00:27:27,084
Is she insane?

416
00:27:29,628 --> 00:27:31,713
Seo-ri, I was so impressed just now.

417
00:27:31,797 --> 00:27:34,716
I've never seen you this confident before.

418
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:38,262
<i>This girl is quite perceptive</i>
<i>for a servant.</i>

419
00:27:38,762 --> 00:27:40,722
<i>I must be more mindful of my words.</i>

420
00:27:43,141 --> 00:27:44,643
I have a plan.

421
00:27:45,686 --> 00:27:47,854
I have decided to take a new path in life.

422
00:27:47,938 --> 00:27:51,233
Is that why you're talking like that?
I see now.

423
00:27:51,316 --> 00:27:53,193
Whatever it is,
it seems like a good strategy.

424
00:27:53,277 --> 00:27:54,736
Stick with it, okay?

425
00:27:59,366 --> 00:28:00,742
Just a second.

426
00:28:01,785 --> 00:28:02,744
Hello?

427
00:28:04,955 --> 00:28:07,499
How is there music coming
from her undergarments?

428
00:28:10,794 --> 00:28:11,920
-Chairman.
-Yes?

429
00:28:13,005 --> 00:28:14,881
A video of the young master's power trip…

430
00:28:14,965 --> 00:28:16,008
What?

431
00:28:17,509 --> 00:28:19,052
That damn brat again?

432
00:28:19,845 --> 00:28:21,054
<i>Just be honest.</i>

433
00:28:21,138 --> 00:28:23,765
<i>Is the chairman still spying on me,</i>
<i>waiting for me to slip up?</i>

434
00:28:23,849 --> 00:28:25,726
It's not spying. It's love.

435
00:28:25,809 --> 00:28:26,977
It's spying.

436
00:28:27,060 --> 00:28:29,104
Keeping tabs on me
because he doesn't trust me

437
00:28:29,187 --> 00:28:31,273
to run a petty shop after moving out.

438
00:28:33,984 --> 00:28:35,027
Is something going on?

439
00:28:35,110 --> 00:28:36,194
What's with this traffic?

440
00:28:36,278 --> 00:28:38,530
There's some sort of solar eclipse show.

441
00:28:38,613 --> 00:28:39,823
It's been chaos all morning.

442
00:28:39,906 --> 00:28:40,782
Unbelievable.

443
00:28:41,658 --> 00:28:43,160
Are we living in the Joseon era?

444
00:28:43,243 --> 00:28:44,661
As if that's such a big deal.

445
00:28:44,745 --> 00:28:47,164
This is why when the news says
people are struggling,

446
00:28:47,247 --> 00:28:48,749
it's a complete lie.

447
00:28:48,832 --> 00:28:51,209
If you're truly struggling,
you're too weak to complain.

448
00:28:51,293 --> 00:28:52,919
<i>I'm exhausted.</i>

449
00:28:53,587 --> 00:28:55,922
She just has me standing
in the hot sun like a statue,

450
00:28:56,006 --> 00:28:57,007
waiting for her.

451
00:28:57,090 --> 00:28:59,343
Just wait until she gets back. I shall…

452
00:29:05,223 --> 00:29:09,227
<i>A branding iron</i>
<i>and even knee-crushing tools…</i>

453
00:29:09,311 --> 00:29:11,521
<i>Is there</i>
<i>a state interrogation underway?</i>

454
00:29:12,814 --> 00:29:15,442
<i>No… this cannot be.</i>

455
00:29:25,243 --> 00:29:27,662
<i>With that many criminals…</i>

456
00:29:33,752 --> 00:29:34,836
<i>This must be…</i>

457
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:37,005
Come on, there's no time! Hurry up!

458
00:29:40,634 --> 00:29:41,885
A rebellion!

459
00:29:44,429 --> 00:29:46,428
GEUNJEONGMUN GATE

460
00:29:48,308 --> 00:29:51,228
A rebellion! A rebellion is afoot!

461
00:29:52,479 --> 00:29:53,814
How are you all so calm?

462
00:30:12,290 --> 00:30:13,917
What in the world…

463
00:30:55,959 --> 00:30:58,670
<i>Pavilions soaring into the sky,</i>

464
00:30:59,337 --> 00:31:00,881
<i>strange attire…</i>

465
00:31:05,260 --> 00:31:08,013
<i>And even palanquins</i>
<i>that run faster than any horse…</i>

466
00:31:13,935 --> 00:31:16,396
<i>All of it is strange and unnatural.</i>

467
00:31:41,796 --> 00:31:43,757
<i>What is this strange new world?</i>

468
00:31:55,435 --> 00:31:57,646
CHA SE-GYE, WHO IS HE REALLY?

469
00:32:05,153 --> 00:32:06,196
CHAEBOL HEIR'S POWER TRIP

470
00:32:08,698 --> 00:32:09,824
<i>A disgrace to the nation.</i>

471
00:32:09,908 --> 00:32:11,159
<i>Can we impeach chaebols?</i>

472
00:32:11,243 --> 00:32:12,619
<i>Punish the violent chaebol.</i>

473
00:32:12,702 --> 00:32:13,954
<i>Boycott Biojei and Chail Group.</i>

474
00:32:14,037 --> 00:32:15,705
<i>Real chaebols have so much class.</i>

475
00:32:15,789 --> 00:32:18,792
<i>He's a half-breed chaebol</i>
<i>with celebrity blood. So low-class.</i>

476
00:32:29,219 --> 00:32:30,512
No easier targets than chaebols.

477
00:32:31,471 --> 00:32:33,306
Sorry? Take it easy?

478
00:32:33,390 --> 00:32:36,643
Easy… Never mind. Just watch the road.

479
00:32:46,027 --> 00:32:48,863
-What was that?
-It was a person…

480
00:32:48,947 --> 00:32:50,365
Are you okay?

481
00:32:53,785 --> 00:32:56,079
Hey, miss. Miss?

482
00:32:59,165 --> 00:33:00,333
Oh, no.

483
00:33:00,959 --> 00:33:02,669
What happened? Did we hit her?

484
00:33:02,752 --> 00:33:04,546
The light changed,
and we were about to go,

485
00:33:04,629 --> 00:33:06,339
when she suddenly collapsed on her own.

486
00:33:07,382 --> 00:33:08,466
Collapsed on her own?

487
00:33:11,595 --> 00:33:13,388
Let's call an ambulance first.

488
00:33:13,471 --> 00:33:15,056
Hell!

489
00:33:23,773 --> 00:33:25,025
Stop right there.

490
00:33:25,108 --> 00:33:27,611
What are you trying to pull here?
Stop right there!

491
00:33:28,612 --> 00:33:29,654
Damn it.

492
00:33:31,906 --> 00:33:33,366
Sir. Wait…

493
00:33:33,450 --> 00:33:34,784
I'll move the car.

494
00:33:37,787 --> 00:33:38,747
Hey!

495
00:33:42,375 --> 00:33:44,836
Where do you think you're going? Damn it.

496
00:33:45,629 --> 00:33:47,464
Have I truly died?

497
00:33:48,131 --> 00:33:50,133
Have I fallen into Avici Hell?

498
00:33:58,058 --> 00:33:59,184
Hell.

499
00:33:59,768 --> 00:34:02,812
Hell… this is hell.

500
00:34:45,855 --> 00:34:47,691
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

501
00:34:47,774 --> 00:34:49,109
And who will they blame?

502
00:34:49,192 --> 00:34:50,402
You think I was born yesterday?

503
00:34:50,485 --> 00:34:51,861
What are you talking about?

504
00:34:51,945 --> 00:34:53,238
Ranting about impeaching chaebols

505
00:34:53,321 --> 00:34:54,531
and filing pointless petitions.

506
00:34:54,614 --> 00:34:56,574
Half-breed chaebol,
national disgrace, or whatever.

507
00:34:56,658 --> 00:34:59,244
Who knows what they'll try
to pin on me next?

508
00:34:59,327 --> 00:35:01,037
"Pin on you"?

509
00:35:01,955 --> 00:35:03,540
How dare you.

510
00:35:03,623 --> 00:35:04,582
You scoundrel!

511
00:35:05,208 --> 00:35:07,669
How dare you run
that filthy mouth of yours!

512
00:35:10,130 --> 00:35:11,464
I think that couple's fighting.

513
00:35:12,966 --> 00:35:15,009
I have never seen such a degenerate.

514
00:35:15,093 --> 00:35:16,428
Where is your sense of propriety?

515
00:35:16,511 --> 00:35:19,472
Even in Avici Hell,
how can you harass a woman like this?

516
00:35:19,556 --> 00:35:21,057
Do you not fear King Yeomra?

517
00:35:22,517 --> 00:35:24,477
King Yeomra? You've got to be kidding me.

518
00:35:25,562 --> 00:35:27,230
You're trying to pull a scam.

519
00:35:27,313 --> 00:35:28,815
Cosplaying like some crazy Joseon woman

520
00:35:28,898 --> 00:35:30,650
to plead insanity.

521
00:35:32,944 --> 00:35:34,612
Just forget it. How much do you want?

522
00:35:34,696 --> 00:35:36,573
Is one bill enough? Or two?

523
00:35:37,824 --> 00:35:39,200
Damn it.

524
00:35:39,284 --> 00:35:41,536
You dare take me for a mere money-grubber?

525
00:35:42,287 --> 00:35:44,247
You good-for-nothing degenerate!

526
00:35:47,292 --> 00:35:49,669
-Have you lost your mind?
-That hurts!

527
00:35:49,753 --> 00:35:51,588
If I am a money-grubber…

528
00:35:51,671 --> 00:35:53,882
-What are you--
-…then you are a lecher!

529
00:35:53,965 --> 00:35:55,925
-You rotten bastard!
-That hurts!

530
00:35:57,010 --> 00:35:57,927
That hurts!

531
00:35:58,011 --> 00:35:59,471
Why, this woman…

532
00:35:59,554 --> 00:36:01,639
That hurts! This woman is totally insane.

533
00:36:07,061 --> 00:36:08,938
-He's fighting back!
-Mom.

534
00:36:09,522 --> 00:36:11,941
Look, they're beating
the crap out of each other.

535
00:36:18,323 --> 00:36:19,282
Hey!

536
00:36:20,366 --> 00:36:21,785
Die! Die already!

537
00:36:27,248 --> 00:36:28,500
Okay, wait a minute. Stop.

538
00:36:28,583 --> 00:36:31,002
Wait! Stop! Freeze, that's enough.

539
00:36:31,108 --> 00:36:32,408
What's with that woman?

540
00:36:37,842 --> 00:36:41,137
I get that you're crazy. I really do.

541
00:36:41,221 --> 00:36:43,014
I lost my mind for a second there too.

542
00:36:43,097 --> 00:36:46,100
This is embarrassing for both of us,
so let's just stop.

543
00:36:46,935 --> 00:36:49,395
I can admit
I'm at least partially responsible.

544
00:36:49,938 --> 00:36:51,564
Just send the medical bill to my company.

545
00:36:53,066 --> 00:36:54,025
What is this?

546
00:36:54,108 --> 00:36:55,360
I assume you have no insurance.

547
00:36:55,443 --> 00:36:58,613
Go get all the X-rays
and MRIs you want while you're at it.

548
00:36:58,696 --> 00:37:00,865
And we'll call it even. Deal?

549
00:37:00,949 --> 00:37:01,908
Damn it.

550
00:37:01,991 --> 00:37:03,201
Damn.

551
00:37:04,536 --> 00:37:05,954
That woman's insane.

552
00:37:06,037 --> 00:37:07,580
What the hell?

553
00:37:15,338 --> 00:37:16,381
Cha Se-gye?

554
00:37:16,464 --> 00:37:18,466
It has a name on it.

555
00:37:18,967 --> 00:37:21,219
Is this some kind of
paper identification tag?

556
00:37:25,854 --> 00:37:28,434
<i>That woman was totally crazy, right?</i>

557
00:37:29,310 --> 00:37:32,188
Right in the middle of the road,
in broad daylight,

558
00:37:32,272 --> 00:37:33,648
she beat me senseless.

559
00:37:33,731 --> 00:37:35,567
I bet she faked that fainting too.

560
00:37:35,650 --> 00:37:37,861
Trying to pull some pathetic scam. Jeez.

561
00:37:37,944 --> 00:37:39,779
She must've panicked
once she was cornered.

562
00:37:39,863 --> 00:37:42,490
Maybe she was trying
to blackmail or scam you?

563
00:37:42,574 --> 00:37:43,825
And the way she talked?

564
00:37:43,908 --> 00:37:46,244
Does she think she is
the queen of Joseon or something?

565
00:37:46,327 --> 00:37:48,705
It seems the New Year's fortune
I saw for you

566
00:37:48,788 --> 00:37:50,582
was right after all.

567
00:37:51,207 --> 00:37:53,167
Why are you looking up
<i>my</i> fortune, Mr. Son?

568
00:37:53,251 --> 00:37:56,713
I'm with you 365 days a year, sir.
Of course I have to.

569
00:37:57,714 --> 00:38:00,216
The shaman said that this is…

570
00:38:01,426 --> 00:38:02,969
a very unlucky year for you.

571
00:38:03,052 --> 00:38:05,096
You must be careful
of water, fire, and women.

572
00:38:05,179 --> 00:38:06,764
Especially women.

573
00:38:06,848 --> 00:38:08,266
Whatever.

574
00:38:08,349 --> 00:38:10,059
I gave that woman my business card,

575
00:38:10,143 --> 00:38:12,103
so you handle the rest.

576
00:38:12,186 --> 00:38:13,771
Just handle the hospital bills.

577
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:17,483
If she causes more trouble,
hand it over to the legal team.

578
00:38:17,567 --> 00:38:18,568
Yes, sir.

579
00:38:19,444 --> 00:38:21,863
Take responsibility
for abusing subcontractors!

580
00:38:21,946 --> 00:38:24,198
Take responsibility
for abusing subcontractors!

581
00:38:24,282 --> 00:38:26,951
Take responsibility
for abusing subcontractors!

582
00:38:27,702 --> 00:38:28,703
What's that about?

583
00:38:28,786 --> 00:38:29,913
Remember that controversy

584
00:38:29,996 --> 00:38:32,624
over abuse of power against
a packaging subcontractor a month ago?

585
00:38:32,707 --> 00:38:35,001
Where the logistics agency made them
install equipment on a whim,

586
00:38:35,084 --> 00:38:36,169
before ending the contract.

587
00:38:36,252 --> 00:38:38,546
Oh, that? That hasn't been resolved yet?

588
00:38:38,630 --> 00:38:42,091
It's all been resolved.
It wasn't a head office matter anyway.

589
00:38:42,175 --> 00:38:45,261
Sir, the director
from Kaiserman Capital has arrived.

590
00:38:47,889 --> 00:38:49,015
Let's go.

591
00:38:51,059 --> 00:38:54,270
Do they not use
Chinese characters here at all?

592
00:38:55,438 --> 00:38:57,982
It is nothing but vernacular script
and squiggles.

593
00:38:58,942 --> 00:39:01,027
Thank goodness I learned
the vernacular script.

594
00:39:01,110 --> 00:39:03,488
I could have ended up illiterate here.

595
00:39:05,448 --> 00:39:07,158
My goodness.

596
00:39:08,117 --> 00:39:10,536
My word. Goodness me.

597
00:39:11,621 --> 00:39:12,622
Goodness.

598
00:39:15,124 --> 00:39:17,627
<i>The pain feels too real</i>

599
00:39:18,211 --> 00:39:20,171
<i>for this to be hell.</i>

600
00:39:21,464 --> 00:39:22,382
Wait.

601
00:39:22,465 --> 00:39:24,859
SUSEONJEONDO

602
00:39:26,552 --> 00:39:29,013
Yes, this is it. Right here.

603
00:39:31,182 --> 00:39:33,101
What a welcome sight.

604
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:36,062
-What is this place?
-Come on.

605
00:39:36,145 --> 00:39:37,230
Here we are.

606
00:39:39,023 --> 00:39:39,899
All right, everyone.

607
00:39:39,983 --> 00:39:43,695
We're going on a trip back in time
to the Joseon dynasty.

608
00:39:43,778 --> 00:39:46,197
Hold hands and follow me.

609
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:47,323
-Okay.
-Okay.

610
00:39:47,949 --> 00:39:49,033
Joseon?

611
00:39:56,958 --> 00:39:59,085
TIME TRAVEL TO THE JOSEON DYNASTY

612
00:40:00,837 --> 00:40:04,674
This painting is a national treasure
from the Joseon dynasty's royal court.

613
00:40:04,757 --> 00:40:05,800
An ink-and-wash painting

614
00:40:05,883 --> 00:40:08,428
from the early reign of King Anjong,
about 300 years ago.

615
00:40:09,637 --> 00:40:10,930
<i>That painting…</i>

616
00:40:20,982 --> 00:40:22,859
Records show
these plum blossoms in the snow

617
00:40:22,942 --> 00:40:24,861
were the work of Queen Onjeong
of the Mun clan.

618
00:40:24,944 --> 00:40:27,238
-Despite her difficult early days…
<i>-But I painted that.</i>

619
00:40:27,321 --> 00:40:30,199
…amid the power struggles,
Queen Onjeong remained composed.

620
00:40:30,283 --> 00:40:32,243
That is not true. The queen?

621
00:40:32,326 --> 00:40:34,912
Who told you
that painting belongs to the queen?

622
00:40:34,996 --> 00:40:36,622
-"Who told me?"
-It is all a lie.

623
00:40:36,706 --> 00:40:39,500
That painting is mine.
How could they say she created it?

624
00:40:39,584 --> 00:40:42,003
Well, historical perspectives

625
00:40:42,086 --> 00:40:43,421
can vary from person to person.

626
00:40:43,504 --> 00:40:47,050
But there's no doubt
this painting belonged to Queen Onjeong.

627
00:40:47,133 --> 00:40:48,718
It's a fact recorded in the Annals.

628
00:40:50,053 --> 00:40:51,721
The Annals?

629
00:40:52,764 --> 00:40:54,891
Do you mean the Annals of the Dynasty?

630
00:40:55,767 --> 00:40:58,269
The Annals are not something
the common people are allowed to see.

631
00:40:58,352 --> 00:41:01,522
If you truly have,
did you see a record of Royal Consort Hui?

632
00:41:01,606 --> 00:41:02,940
A record of Lady Kang Dan-sim?

633
00:41:04,025 --> 00:41:05,860
-Kang Dan-sim?
-The villainess.

634
00:41:07,445 --> 00:41:08,738
Is she looking for attention?

635
00:41:08,821 --> 00:41:10,531
-A villainess.
-Well,

636
00:41:10,615 --> 00:41:13,659
women's names aren't
in the official Joseon historical records,

637
00:41:13,743 --> 00:41:16,537
but Lady Kang, who was executed
by poisoning and stripped of her title

638
00:41:16,621 --> 00:41:19,332
during the Gyeongsul Political Purge,
is pretty well known.

639
00:41:19,415 --> 00:41:20,625
"Stripped of her title"?

640
00:41:21,918 --> 00:41:23,127
"Executed by poisoning"?

641
00:41:24,253 --> 00:41:25,880
So I really died?

642
00:41:25,963 --> 00:41:30,009
In any case, no records or artifacts
from royal concubines have survived.

643
00:41:30,093 --> 00:41:31,719
Okay, everyone, shall we head this way?

644
00:41:31,803 --> 00:41:33,387
Follow me.

645
00:41:41,979 --> 00:41:43,773
Nothing at all?

646
00:41:52,198 --> 00:41:54,992
TIME TRAVEL TO THE JOSEON DYNASTY

647
00:42:15,179 --> 00:42:17,306
<i>Stripped of her title. Death by poisoning.</i>

648
00:42:18,057 --> 00:42:19,851
<i>Have I truly died?</i>

649
00:42:21,269 --> 00:42:22,478
Excuse me.

650
00:42:23,187 --> 00:42:24,188
Excuse me!

651
00:42:26,065 --> 00:42:29,443
I overheard your refreshing insight
on Royal Consort Hui of the Kang Clan.

652
00:42:29,527 --> 00:42:33,197
I'm writing my thesis on reinterpreting
the infamous villainess, you see.

653
00:42:33,281 --> 00:42:35,700
That's why I was so excited
to hear you speak.

654
00:42:36,951 --> 00:42:38,161
Are you a graduate student?

655
00:42:38,244 --> 00:42:41,831
Tell me, what do you know
of Royal Consort Hui of the Kang clan?

656
00:42:41,914 --> 00:42:43,749
Gosh, the way you speak…

657
00:42:43,833 --> 00:42:45,918
Your dedication is on another level.

658
00:42:48,004 --> 00:42:51,382
It's not in the official records,
but according to unofficial histories…

659
00:42:55,553 --> 00:42:57,346
They said she was second
only to the king

660
00:42:57,430 --> 00:42:58,639
and that the world was hers.

661
00:42:58,723 --> 00:43:00,892
But that commoner's time will soon be up.

662
00:43:00,975 --> 00:43:02,518
Do you not agree, Your Majesty?

663
00:43:02,602 --> 00:43:06,439
<i>Despite her low birth, she'd often beat</i>
<i>the noble-born concubines.</i>

664
00:43:06,522 --> 00:43:09,150
<i>She was notorious as a wicked woman</i>
<i>who taught them harsh lessons.</i>

665
00:43:09,233 --> 00:43:11,068
Have you heard anything?

666
00:43:11,152 --> 00:43:14,697
Well, Lady Kang claims she's praying
for the royal family's fortune.

667
00:43:14,780 --> 00:43:16,407
But who knows for sure?

668
00:43:17,283 --> 00:43:20,244
It could be a curse meant
to bring about the Queen's death.

669
00:43:20,328 --> 00:43:21,204
Oh, my.

670
00:43:21,287 --> 00:43:22,955
That is what I am saying!

671
00:43:23,039 --> 00:43:24,749
This blasted drought!

672
00:43:24,832 --> 00:43:27,251
It is all because of that wench,
that Royal Consort Hui!

673
00:43:27,335 --> 00:43:31,464
Since that concubine took power,
every man has been chasing skirts.

674
00:43:31,547 --> 00:43:33,382
<i>With a wicked woman</i>
<i>manipulating the throne,</i>

675
00:43:33,466 --> 00:43:35,051
<i>the barbarians grew restless,</i>

676
00:43:35,134 --> 00:43:37,595
<i>the harvests failed, plagues spread,</i>

677
00:43:37,678 --> 00:43:39,639
<i>and the droughts became deadly.</i>
<i>They were like…</i>

678
00:43:39,722 --> 00:43:40,848
These are the end times.

679
00:43:40,932 --> 00:43:42,767
Right? She is nothing but lowborn.

680
00:43:43,517 --> 00:43:45,561
Just another lowborn.

681
00:43:45,645 --> 00:43:48,856
<i>She was disliked on a cataclysmic level.</i>

682
00:43:56,572 --> 00:43:57,782
<i>Kang Dan-sim?</i>

683
00:43:58,324 --> 00:44:02,161
<i>Well, women's names aren't</i>
<i>in the official Joseon historical records,</i>

684
00:44:02,245 --> 00:44:06,916
<i>but Lady Kang, who was executed</i>
<i>by poisoning and stripped of her title…</i>

685
00:44:06,999 --> 00:44:09,001
<i>I have no name to call my own,</i>

686
00:44:09,085 --> 00:44:11,796
<i>and my body is already dead from poison.</i>

687
00:44:12,880 --> 00:44:16,550
<i>And I have become a villainess</i>
<i>even children mock.</i>

688
00:44:19,136 --> 00:44:21,847
<i>After 300 years,</i>
<i>is all that remains of me in Joseon</i>

689
00:44:22,598 --> 00:44:25,685
<i>a stigma that will not wash away,</i>
<i>even in death?</i>

690
00:44:25,768 --> 00:44:27,645
According to them…

691
00:44:30,523 --> 00:44:33,234
even if I were stoned to death
a hundred times,

692
00:44:34,986 --> 00:44:37,154
I am a wench who deserved it all.

693
00:44:45,204 --> 00:44:49,041
My goodness, Your Majesty.

694
00:44:56,257 --> 00:44:59,802
What brings such an esteemed person here?

695
00:45:01,887 --> 00:45:05,057
Do you recognize me?

696
00:45:08,102 --> 00:45:10,896
You have the face of a queen.

697
00:45:12,898 --> 00:45:14,859
Do not even mention
that word in my presence.

698
00:45:16,610 --> 00:45:20,573
The throne alone
does not confer regal bearing.

699
00:45:20,656 --> 00:45:25,619
Just like how merely occupying
the role of father does not make him one.

700
00:45:35,463 --> 00:45:36,964
Did you say 400 years?

701
00:45:37,048 --> 00:45:38,174
It has been 300 years.

702
00:45:38,257 --> 00:45:41,135
My body died, leaving only my spirit.

703
00:45:41,218 --> 00:45:43,637
Are you saying
you can reverse 300 years of time?

704
00:45:47,516 --> 00:45:50,895
I have heard all about necromancy
from the royal shamans.

705
00:45:51,437 --> 00:45:53,397
Logically, if you can summon one,

706
00:45:53,481 --> 00:45:56,025
then sending one back
should not be impossible.

707
00:45:57,068 --> 00:45:58,694
Yes, about that…

708
00:45:58,778 --> 00:46:02,198
Actually, in this line of work,
it's a fairly common occurrence.

709
00:46:02,281 --> 00:46:05,743
From Goguryeo, Baekje,
Silla, Joseon, you name it.

710
00:46:05,826 --> 00:46:09,080
Someone from each era shows up
just when you've forgotten.

711
00:46:09,163 --> 00:46:10,539
-From each era?
-Yes.

712
00:46:10,623 --> 00:46:13,709
It's a classic tale at this point.

713
00:46:13,793 --> 00:46:16,212
It's a story we hear
time and again, you see?

714
00:46:16,295 --> 00:46:18,923
Just 20 years ago,

715
00:46:19,006 --> 00:46:21,967
there was a princess
who flew in from Buyeo.

716
00:46:22,051 --> 00:46:23,552
It was called <i>Thousand Years of Love.</i>

717
00:46:23,636 --> 00:46:26,389
"I am Princess Buyeo Ju
from Southern Buyeo!"

718
00:46:26,472 --> 00:46:27,890
Gosh,

719
00:46:27,973 --> 00:46:31,268
that show was a huge hit 20 years ago.

720
00:46:34,522 --> 00:46:37,316
Maybe that's too old for you?
In that case,

721
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:39,985
how about <i>Rooftop Prince?</i>

722
00:46:40,069 --> 00:46:41,404
Or maybe <i>Queen In-hyun's Man?</i>

723
00:46:41,487 --> 00:46:43,406
Good heavens! How dare you?

724
00:46:43,489 --> 00:46:45,950
A man other than the king?
Do you have a death wish?

725
00:46:46,033 --> 00:46:49,203
You know, I was just saying.
I didn't mean anything by it.

726
00:46:49,286 --> 00:46:52,581
You don't seem to understand
how things work around here.

727
00:46:52,665 --> 00:46:55,876
No, I had my suspicions.

728
00:46:56,627 --> 00:46:59,380
I have read books
like <i>Yongjaechonghwa </i>and <i>Eou Yadam.</i>

729
00:47:00,005 --> 00:47:02,508
I have also read my share
of tales about mythical creatures.

730
00:47:02,591 --> 00:47:05,761
I figured there was more to this world
than what meets the eye.

731
00:47:05,845 --> 00:47:07,930
I have had such suspicions for some time.

732
00:47:12,518 --> 00:47:15,187
Your Majesty, pardon me for a second.

733
00:47:23,112 --> 00:47:25,948
Your Majesty,
this isn't spirit possession.

734
00:47:26,031 --> 00:47:27,324
Possession, time travel.

735
00:47:29,743 --> 00:47:33,706
I believe it's more like time wandering.

736
00:47:33,789 --> 00:47:35,958
Possession, time wandering?

737
00:47:37,168 --> 00:47:38,252
What is the difference?

738
00:47:38,335 --> 00:47:40,713
Well, if you want to get technical,

739
00:47:40,796 --> 00:47:43,048
there is a difference. A big one.

740
00:47:43,132 --> 00:47:45,843
But the fact that your spirit

741
00:47:45,926 --> 00:47:50,222
is living in that woman's body
makes them more or less the same.

742
00:47:52,558 --> 00:47:55,352
Your Majesty, do you understand?

743
00:47:57,271 --> 00:47:58,355
How wondrous it is indeed.

744
00:48:02,276 --> 00:48:06,655
My current situation
is just like an old folktale.

745
00:48:07,573 --> 00:48:08,449
Pardon me?

746
00:48:08,532 --> 00:48:11,327
Zhuangzi dreamed he was a butterfly.

747
00:48:12,369 --> 00:48:14,330
Was Zhuangzi the butterfly,

748
00:48:15,331 --> 00:48:16,499
or was the butterfly Zhuangzi?

749
00:48:18,501 --> 00:48:20,419
My 20 years of life…

750
00:48:21,837 --> 00:48:24,507
are now a bygone tale from 300 years ago.

751
00:48:25,508 --> 00:48:27,551
You're a genius.

752
00:48:27,635 --> 00:48:31,430
To grasp such a difficult concept
in one go.

753
00:48:31,514 --> 00:48:34,808
Your adaptability is at max level.

754
00:49:27,820 --> 00:49:29,071
<i>You scoundrel!</i>

755
00:49:29,154 --> 00:49:32,116
How dare you run
that filthy mouth of yours!

756
00:49:32,199 --> 00:49:33,784
I have never seen such a degenerate.

757
00:50:11,614 --> 00:50:14,074
Those posts went viral a while ago.

758
00:50:14,158 --> 00:50:16,118
The ones about how to date a chaebol.

759
00:50:16,201 --> 00:50:17,620
A method like that exists?

760
00:50:17,703 --> 00:50:20,414
How to date a chaebol. It's simple.

761
00:50:20,497 --> 00:50:21,749
Find a chaebol.

762
00:50:21,832 --> 00:50:24,043
Slap them. Date them.

763
00:50:24,752 --> 00:50:26,378
What on earth is
the mechanism behind that?

764
00:50:26,462 --> 00:50:29,340
Why would you suddenly start dating
someone who slapped you?

765
00:50:29,423 --> 00:50:32,259
"You're the first woman
who's ever treated me like this."

766
00:50:32,343 --> 00:50:33,636
"It's refreshing."

767
00:50:34,511 --> 00:50:35,721
"It's thrilling."

768
00:50:36,847 --> 00:50:38,974
-That's ridiculous.
-Hold on.

769
00:50:39,058 --> 00:50:40,768
Come to think of it,
that woman from before

770
00:50:40,851 --> 00:50:42,811
hit all three in one go.

771
00:50:42,895 --> 00:50:45,272
Find a chaebol, slap them.

772
00:50:45,356 --> 00:50:46,690
Date…

773
00:50:51,820 --> 00:50:53,781
-Mr. Son.
-Sir.

774
00:50:53,864 --> 00:50:55,074
I'm warning you.

775
00:50:55,157 --> 00:50:58,118
Don't you ever even breathe
a word about that woman again.

776
00:51:11,715 --> 00:51:14,134
<i>When I was in full bloom,</i>

777
00:51:14,218 --> 00:51:16,637
<i>I thought I would stay</i>
<i>that way forever.</i>

778
00:51:19,098 --> 00:51:20,808
So beautiful.

779
00:51:24,812 --> 00:51:29,566
<i>Looking back,</i>
<i>my life was but an empty dream.</i>

780
00:51:29,650 --> 00:51:32,069
<i>A fleeting, beautiful moment.</i>

781
00:51:37,241 --> 00:51:39,326
<i>I lost my way.</i>

782
00:51:39,410 --> 00:51:42,037
<i>Cast out into a new world,</i>

783
00:51:42,121 --> 00:51:44,540
<i>neither paradise nor hell.</i>

784
00:51:45,124 --> 00:51:50,003
<i>Is this, then, a punishment</i>
<i>from the heavens?</i>

785
00:51:59,638 --> 00:52:01,473
<i>Right now in downtown Seoul,</i>

786
00:52:01,557 --> 00:52:04,393
<i>an unforecasted shower</i>
<i>is suddenly pouring down.</i>

787
00:52:04,476 --> 00:52:06,979
<i>And because of that,</i>
<i>our message board is flooded</i>

788
00:52:07,062 --> 00:52:09,857
<i>with complaints from listeners</i>
<i>who forgot their umbrellas.</i>

789
00:52:10,649 --> 00:52:13,235
<i>It seems this surprise sun shower</i>
<i>on a dull afternoon</i>

790
00:52:13,318 --> 00:52:15,112
<i>isn't very welcome.</i>

791
00:52:15,195 --> 00:52:17,239
<i>But did you know?</i>

792
00:52:17,322 --> 00:52:21,952
<i>An unwelcome sun shower</i>
<i>can represent unspoken feelings.</i>

793
00:52:23,328 --> 00:52:25,372
<i>You all know the origin</i>
<i>of the sun shower, don't you?</i>

794
00:52:25,456 --> 00:52:27,958
<i>A fox was marrying a tiger,</i>

795
00:52:28,041 --> 00:52:31,420
<i>and a cloud that loved her</i>
<i>shed tears of sorrow.</i>

796
00:52:31,503 --> 00:52:34,465
<i>But they say there's another,</i>
<i>truer meaning.</i>

797
00:52:35,966 --> 00:52:38,093
COMET FOR FIRST TIME IN 300 YEARS

798
00:52:38,177 --> 00:52:41,764
<i>The true meaning of a sun shower is…</i>

799
00:53:00,532 --> 00:53:02,201
I am cold.

800
00:53:20,177 --> 00:53:21,595
I am alive.

801
00:53:22,304 --> 00:53:23,764
<i>I survived.</i>

802
00:53:36,401 --> 00:53:39,071
<i>I do not care if this is</i>
<i>a reward or punishment.</i>

803
00:53:39,947 --> 00:53:41,573
<i>What does any of it matter?</i>

804
00:53:49,289 --> 00:53:51,375
<i>I am filled with profound gratitude</i>

805
00:53:51,458 --> 00:53:54,253
<i>simply to be alive thus, rather than dead.</i>

806
00:54:00,759 --> 00:54:04,221
<i>No, this is not a curse.</i>

807
00:54:04,304 --> 00:54:06,348
<i>Let me think of it as a rebirth.</i>

808
00:54:07,057 --> 00:54:11,061
<i>Not a punishment, but a second chance.</i>

809
00:54:11,728 --> 00:54:14,064
<i>It may be wretched, but I survived.</i>

810
00:54:15,023 --> 00:54:16,316
<i>So in this life…</i>

811
00:54:16,400 --> 00:54:17,943
I shall live as I please.

812
00:54:18,652 --> 00:54:20,654
And consider this a reward.

813
00:54:30,372 --> 00:54:31,582
I'll go when the rain eases.

814
00:54:31,665 --> 00:54:34,585
Excuse me. If I wish to find
the owner of this identification tag,

815
00:54:34,668 --> 00:54:35,627
what must I do?

816
00:54:38,213 --> 00:54:41,466
<i>The true meaning of a sun shower is</i>

817
00:54:41,550 --> 00:54:45,220
<i>that it comes so that the one you love</i>
<i>may live a new and happy life.</i>

818
00:54:45,304 --> 00:54:46,555
<i>It's a blessing sent</i>

819
00:54:46,638 --> 00:54:49,182
<i>while shedding tears of sorrow.</i>

820
00:54:49,850 --> 00:54:51,643
<i>The rain has stopped, and like a gift,</i>

821
00:54:51,727 --> 00:54:53,520
<i>a rainbow has appeared over the city.</i>

822
00:54:53,604 --> 00:54:56,565
<i>The misfortune of the rain.</i>
<i>The good fortune of the rainbow.</i>

823
00:54:56,648 --> 00:55:00,068
<i>Which of the two would you choose?</i>

824
00:55:08,493 --> 00:55:13,373
<i>Even without any powerful backing,</i>
<i>I rose to the top of the Inner Court.</i>

825
00:55:13,457 --> 00:55:17,044
<i>Here, there is no king,</i>
<i>shamaness, or minister</i>

826
00:55:17,127 --> 00:55:18,503
<i>to do my bidding.</i>

827
00:55:20,005 --> 00:55:23,717
<i>Then there is only one way</i>
<i>for me to survive here.</i>

828
00:55:28,986 --> 00:55:31,183
<i>He may be an ill-mannered degenerate,</i>

829
00:55:31,266 --> 00:55:34,102
<i>but he looks like</i>
<i>he has never bowed down to anyone.</i>

830
00:55:34,186 --> 00:55:37,147
<i>Everything from the arrogance in his eyes</i>
<i>to the tone in which he speaks,</i>

831
00:55:37,230 --> 00:55:40,567
<i>and even the way he carries himself,</i>
<i>practically oozes wealth.</i>

832
00:55:40,651 --> 00:55:43,612
<i>I am certain he must be</i>
<i>a man of considerable influence.</i>

833
00:55:46,448 --> 00:55:48,200
Starting today,

834
00:55:48,742 --> 00:55:52,496
I shall use you as my sword and shield.

835
00:56:08,720 --> 00:56:10,305
Mr. Son. It's the chairman.

836
00:56:13,600 --> 00:56:16,311
Mr. Chairman, I wasn't told
you were coming--

837
00:56:23,610 --> 00:56:26,363
Swinging a bat? What are you, a thug?

838
00:56:26,947 --> 00:56:28,323
<i>You </i>stormed out on us.

839
00:56:28,407 --> 00:56:30,826
So why are you trashing Mun-do's company?

840
00:56:30,909 --> 00:56:35,205
I was actually going to tell you
at your birthday party later.

841
00:56:35,288 --> 00:56:37,541
Grandfather, it's a deepfake.
It's doctored.

842
00:56:37,624 --> 00:56:39,084
Give me a break, you punk!

843
00:56:39,167 --> 00:56:42,546
Look here. That is clearly your face.

844
00:56:42,629 --> 00:56:43,922
I was shocked at first too.

845
00:56:44,006 --> 00:56:45,966
I thought I had amnesia or something.

846
00:56:46,049 --> 00:56:47,509
It looks so much like me.

847
00:56:48,802 --> 00:56:50,429
Do you hear yourself right now?

848
00:56:50,512 --> 00:56:52,931
That you're even confused is the problem!

849
00:56:53,015 --> 00:56:54,141
You always said

850
00:56:54,224 --> 00:56:57,102
a businessman finds
opportunity in a crisis.

851
00:56:57,185 --> 00:56:59,438
I already made them an acquisition offer.

852
00:56:59,521 --> 00:57:01,189
We're meeting this week.

853
00:57:02,190 --> 00:57:04,026
Their tech is on par with Hollywood.

854
00:57:04,109 --> 00:57:06,361
You money-grubbing punk!

855
00:57:06,445 --> 00:57:08,488
Everything's an acquisition
or a sale to you.

856
00:57:08,572 --> 00:57:11,783
You go on matchmaking dates
and just talk money.

857
00:57:11,867 --> 00:57:13,285
I never told you to do that.

858
00:57:13,368 --> 00:57:14,411
But I have to.

859
00:57:14,494 --> 00:57:16,329
Marriage is a crucial merger in life.

860
00:57:16,872 --> 00:57:17,748
SONGHWA MULSAN

861
00:57:17,849 --> 00:57:19,791
My father is
also a businessman, like you.

862
00:57:19,875 --> 00:57:21,793
You've heard of Songhwa Mulsan, right?

863
00:57:21,877 --> 00:57:23,795
Yes. He was on the news yesterday,
in a wheelchair.

864
00:57:23,879 --> 00:57:25,172
Embezzlement and breach of trust?

865
00:57:25,255 --> 00:57:27,132
If you're looking to use marriage

866
00:57:27,215 --> 00:57:29,217
to fill the void while the chairman
is in the slammer,

867
00:57:29,301 --> 00:57:31,094
then I'm all for that merger.

868
00:57:32,721 --> 00:57:34,264
I'll give you three days.

869
00:57:34,890 --> 00:57:36,224
I guess you enjoy dark humor?

870
00:57:36,308 --> 00:57:37,289
SQ RETAIL

871
00:57:37,414 --> 00:57:38,935
The company promotes
an eco-friendly image,

872
00:57:39,019 --> 00:57:40,729
but its chairman's daughter
is a fur lover?

873
00:57:40,812 --> 00:57:42,147
Is that polar bear fur? Growl.

874
00:57:42,230 --> 00:57:44,566
It's a proposal
for my company's new brand.

875
00:57:44,649 --> 00:57:47,069
Our relationship will depend
on the size of the investment.

876
00:57:50,697 --> 00:57:52,407
Your dream is to be
a stew-cooking housewife?

877
00:57:52,491 --> 00:57:55,327
I prefer toast to stew.
And a business partner to a doting wife.

878
00:57:55,410 --> 00:57:57,704
So keep your stake in the holding company
even after we get married.

879
00:57:57,788 --> 00:57:59,915
Or better yet, sign it over to me.

880
00:58:02,667 --> 00:58:04,586
Do you know what they call you
behind your back?

881
00:58:04,669 --> 00:58:05,754
Marriage-alliance wrecker!

882
00:58:07,047 --> 00:58:09,216
That's still better
than "half-breed chaebol."

883
00:58:09,299 --> 00:58:11,301
My mom provided me
with only a humble background.

884
00:58:11,384 --> 00:58:12,761
Me looking to marry up?

885
00:58:12,844 --> 00:58:14,346
It's only natural, Grandfather.

886
00:58:14,429 --> 00:58:17,390
I plan on selling myself
to the highest bidder.

887
00:58:17,974 --> 00:58:20,435
Once this launch is a success,

888
00:58:20,519 --> 00:58:22,062
women will be flocking to me.

889
00:58:22,145 --> 00:58:23,688
Why you little…

890
00:58:24,773 --> 00:58:26,024
Unbelievable.

891
00:58:34,741 --> 00:58:37,244
OPEN CASTING CALL FOR MODELS

892
00:58:37,327 --> 00:58:39,454
SEEKING THE QUEEN OF DYNAESTIE

893
00:58:48,713 --> 00:58:51,466
It appears they will accept
any riffraff here.

894
00:58:51,967 --> 00:58:54,386
Whether in Joseon or here,
the powerful ones…

895
00:58:55,303 --> 00:58:57,222
are all the same.

896
00:59:08,400 --> 00:59:10,277
May I help you?

897
00:59:10,360 --> 00:59:12,028
I have come to meet your superior.

898
00:59:12,112 --> 00:59:13,155
Please inform him.

899
00:59:13,780 --> 00:59:15,282
The CEO?

900
00:59:15,365 --> 00:59:16,575
And what is your name?

901
00:59:16,658 --> 00:59:18,493
Kang Dan-sim…

902
00:59:20,412 --> 00:59:21,913
<i>Shin Seo-ri, are you nuts?</i>

903
00:59:21,997 --> 00:59:23,874
-Seo-ri, you've been…
-Shin Seo-ri, you…

904
00:59:26,251 --> 00:59:28,503
Shin… Seo-ri?

905
00:59:28,587 --> 00:59:31,423
Ms. Shin Seo-ri?
What time is your appointment?

906
00:59:31,506 --> 00:59:33,675
I did not make an appointment,

907
00:59:33,758 --> 00:59:36,636
but I was told to come
with this paper identification tag.

908
00:59:37,179 --> 00:59:38,388
DYNAESTIE MODEL CASTING CALL

909
00:59:39,055 --> 00:59:41,433
So that's why you're talking like that.

910
00:59:41,975 --> 00:59:45,979
The audition is around the corner.
Just follow the other applicants.

911
00:59:46,062 --> 00:59:47,069
SHIN SEO-RI

912
00:59:47,144 --> 00:59:48,565
I wish you luck.

913
00:59:51,193 --> 00:59:52,611
Thank you.

914
00:59:57,490 --> 00:59:58,992
Sir.

915
01:00:00,535 --> 01:00:02,913
My head is spinning right now.

916
01:00:02,996 --> 01:00:05,457
Next time my grandfather shows up,
tell him I'm out.

917
01:00:05,540 --> 01:00:06,791
Yes, sir.

918
01:00:06,875 --> 01:00:08,293
What about the audition?

919
01:00:08,376 --> 01:00:10,045
Director Jang is running it,

920
01:00:10,128 --> 01:00:12,088
and he asked if you'll be observing.

921
01:00:12,172 --> 01:00:14,216
Do I really need to get involved?

922
01:00:14,299 --> 01:00:17,010
Have the team screen them first,
then bring me the finalists.

923
01:00:17,928 --> 01:00:19,179
Understood.

924
01:00:19,679 --> 01:00:22,599
Sir, about that protester from earlier--

925
01:00:22,682 --> 01:00:24,226
Can it wait?

926
01:00:24,309 --> 01:00:25,977
I need to make a call.

927
01:00:26,645 --> 01:00:27,729
Yes, sir.

928
01:00:36,071 --> 01:00:42,986
STAND UNITED AND FIGHT

929
01:00:46,164 --> 01:00:47,396
SHIN SEO-RI

930
01:00:48,583 --> 01:00:49,876
<i>My word.</i>

931
01:00:49,960 --> 01:00:53,255
<i>He is no king,</i>
<i>yet he summons people at will.</i>

932
01:00:53,797 --> 01:00:55,966
<i>How many hours must I wait?</i>

933
01:01:04,641 --> 01:01:08,561
<i>Damn degenerate. He must be</i>
<i>more powerful than I thought.</i>

934
01:01:08,645 --> 01:01:10,146
I have come to the right place.

935
01:01:14,901 --> 01:01:17,654
-Oh my, are we a bit late?
-It's Yoon Ji-hyo. It's her.

936
01:01:17,737 --> 01:01:20,365
-It's Yoon Ji-hyo.
-I'm so sorry. Traffic was terrible.

937
01:01:20,448 --> 01:01:23,201
Did she have someone tailing me?

938
01:01:23,285 --> 01:01:24,286
What are those two…

939
01:01:24,369 --> 01:01:26,371
Sir, if you have a moment,

940
01:01:26,454 --> 01:01:28,248
can we have a quick chat?

941
01:01:28,331 --> 01:01:29,457
YOON JI-HYO

942
01:01:36,214 --> 01:01:38,883
Shin Seo-ri, what are you doing here?

943
01:01:38,967 --> 01:01:42,345
If you are late, do not cut in line.
Go to the back.

944
01:01:43,888 --> 01:01:47,017
You ditch a shoot in the morning
to show up for an afternoon audition?

945
01:01:47,100 --> 01:01:50,770
Seo-ri, you are one busy bee today.

946
01:01:51,396 --> 01:01:53,273
I think that as well.

947
01:01:55,734 --> 01:01:59,029
Isn't it a bit pathetic
to be so two-faced?

948
01:01:59,112 --> 01:02:02,198
You used to criticize actors
for selling out for commercials.

949
01:02:02,282 --> 01:02:05,201
But now that you're without an agency
and totally washed up,

950
01:02:05,285 --> 01:02:07,329
you're ready to hit the ground running?

951
01:02:07,412 --> 01:02:09,497
You are right.
I do need to hit the ground.

952
01:02:09,581 --> 01:02:11,750
I am here to properly ground myself.

953
01:02:12,334 --> 01:02:14,336
So let us just mind our own business.

954
01:02:15,045 --> 01:02:18,173
Seeing your face
does not exactly brighten my day either.

955
01:02:18,256 --> 01:02:21,843
I don't know how you've hidden
that sharp tongue until now.

956
01:02:23,011 --> 01:02:25,805
But Seo-ri, this whole audition thing

957
01:02:25,889 --> 01:02:28,058
isn't something you can win with bluffing.

958
01:02:29,184 --> 01:02:31,269
<i>Has this wench lost her damn mind?</i>

959
01:02:31,353 --> 01:02:33,688
<i>She has been picking fights</i>
<i>over every little thing.</i>

960
01:02:34,439 --> 01:02:38,193
Look. All the aces from every top agency
in the country are here.

961
01:02:38,276 --> 01:02:41,071
I'm almost worried
that you might be too relaxed.

962
01:02:41,154 --> 01:02:43,406
I just came to see a degenerate.

963
01:02:43,490 --> 01:02:46,076
Why would I need to be tense for that?

964
01:02:46,159 --> 01:02:47,744
You worry about the strangest things.

965
01:02:47,827 --> 01:02:49,079
Damn, she's so confident.

966
01:02:51,414 --> 01:02:53,124
You know what they say.

967
01:02:53,208 --> 01:02:56,169
"Everyone has a plan

968
01:02:56,252 --> 01:02:58,338
until they get smacked in the face."

969
01:02:58,421 --> 01:03:00,882
So I applaud your reckless courage.

970
01:03:01,841 --> 01:03:05,220
<i>A staring contest? I cannot possibly lose.</i>

971
01:03:08,681 --> 01:03:11,768
"When the work is done, retire."
Wise words from <i>Tao Te Ching.</i>

972
01:03:11,851 --> 01:03:13,478
I will gladly applaud you as well.

973
01:03:14,136 --> 01:03:15,200
Now,

974
01:03:15,397 --> 01:03:16,356
begone!

975
01:03:21,403 --> 01:03:23,029
The next group can go in now.

976
01:03:28,493 --> 01:03:30,412
I'd like to ask
what sort of mindset led you

977
01:03:30,495 --> 01:03:32,872
to come to this audition at Biojei today.

978
01:03:32,956 --> 01:03:36,042
"Where there's a will, there's a way."
I'm here with the spirit of a rookie.

979
01:03:36,126 --> 01:03:38,336
I'm here today,
feeling pleasantly nervous.

980
01:03:38,420 --> 01:03:42,882
I feel excited
as if I were meeting my first love.

981
01:03:42,966 --> 01:03:44,968
Ready to risk it all.
A matter of life and death.

982
01:03:45,051 --> 01:03:47,971
I have come prepared to die
if this is not my path.

983
01:03:48,054 --> 01:03:49,764
Gosh, there's no need to go that far.

984
01:03:49,848 --> 01:03:53,143
Well, having such strong resolve
isn't a bad thing.

985
01:03:53,226 --> 01:03:57,147
All right. Can you tell us
where you see yourselves

986
01:03:57,230 --> 01:03:58,356
in ten years?

987
01:03:58,440 --> 01:04:01,109
I think I'll be
with my loving husband and children,

988
01:04:01,192 --> 01:04:03,445
cooking up soybean paste stew for them.

989
01:04:03,528 --> 01:04:06,906
I mean, I'm sure I'll still be working
in the entertainment industry.

990
01:04:07,615 --> 01:04:12,120
To be honest, my childhood dream
was to be a good wife and a wise mother.

991
01:04:12,203 --> 01:04:14,789
Even a queen, in front of her family,

992
01:04:14,873 --> 01:04:17,709
is just an ordinary person, right?

993
01:04:19,377 --> 01:04:21,880
To be born a woman,
only to squat by the kitchen stove

994
01:04:21,963 --> 01:04:24,340
and dream of serving up stew.

995
01:04:25,300 --> 01:04:27,010
What a pathetic excuse for a dream.

996
01:04:27,093 --> 01:04:28,303
"Pathetic"?

997
01:04:28,386 --> 01:04:32,223
"Good wife and wise mother.
Ordinary person."

998
01:04:32,307 --> 01:04:34,100
It will all be in vain.

999
01:04:34,184 --> 01:04:36,436
The world has changed so much,
yet you would volunteer

1000
01:04:36,519 --> 01:04:37,937
to be a kitchen maid.

1001
01:04:38,021 --> 01:04:41,316
If our foremothers like Heo Nanseolheon
and Shin Saimdang were to hear this,

1002
01:04:41,399 --> 01:04:42,984
they would rise from their graves weeping.

1003
01:04:43,067 --> 01:04:45,445
Gosh, don't you think
that's taking it a bit too far?

1004
01:04:45,528 --> 01:04:47,739
But didn't the scholar, Im Yunjidang,
say as much?

1005
01:04:47,822 --> 01:04:50,408
That the natures of men and women
are not inherently different.

1006
01:04:50,492 --> 01:04:54,871
As for me, in this life,
I would choose to remain unmarried.

1007
01:04:54,954 --> 01:04:56,706
And I would devote myself to my studies

1008
01:04:56,789 --> 01:04:59,542
to rise to the top
of whatever field it may be.

1009
01:05:00,376 --> 01:05:02,545
Sounds like a Gen Z manifesto.

1010
01:05:03,796 --> 01:05:04,881
You scoundrel!

1011
01:05:07,592 --> 01:05:09,302
What are you doing here?

1012
01:05:09,844 --> 01:05:12,472
I have come to offer you a deal.

1013
01:05:21,189 --> 01:05:23,900
-Do you know her?
-No, not really.

1014
01:05:23,983 --> 01:05:26,819
Don't mind me.
Just continue with what you were doing.

1015
01:05:37,872 --> 01:05:40,917
<i>My moniker is the Lion Dog of the Annex.</i>

1016
01:05:42,252 --> 01:05:44,879
<i>Once I sink my teeth in, I never let go.</i>

1017
01:05:52,345 --> 01:05:53,721
What now?

1018
01:05:53,805 --> 01:05:55,515
Do you have more business with me?

1019
01:05:57,600 --> 01:06:00,186
Did I not tell you
I have a deal to offer you?

1020
01:06:00,270 --> 01:06:02,855
Normally, in a deal,
you first need to have something

1021
01:06:02,939 --> 01:06:04,774
the other person wants.

1022
01:06:05,858 --> 01:06:07,193
But you…

1023
01:06:10,321 --> 01:06:11,364
SHIN SEO-RI

1024
01:06:12,282 --> 01:06:15,577
You, Ms. Shin Seo-ri,
seem to have absolutely nothing.

1025
01:06:16,452 --> 01:06:18,538
Do you judge people by appearances alone?

1026
01:06:18,621 --> 01:06:21,124
Managing your own image is a skill too.

1027
01:06:21,833 --> 01:06:23,459
<i>"Image-ma"?</i>

1028
01:06:23,543 --> 01:06:25,920
<i>You wish to use fancy words? Very well.</i>

1029
01:06:26,004 --> 01:06:28,756
They say the art of compassion
is itself a divine art.

1030
01:06:28,840 --> 01:06:30,800
If you only judge people
by their appearance,

1031
01:06:30,883 --> 01:06:32,760
how will you ever recruit talented people

1032
01:06:32,844 --> 01:06:36,931
and become the most powerful man
in this country…

1033
01:06:38,474 --> 01:06:39,892
That scoundrel.

1034
01:06:44,355 --> 01:06:46,357
Hey! I was speaking to you!

1035
01:06:46,441 --> 01:06:49,277
Such conduct would be deemed
improper in any culture.

1036
01:06:51,529 --> 01:06:54,407
If I'm not getting anything out of this,
isn't this just a waste of time?

1037
01:06:54,490 --> 01:06:56,284
I have not even begun
to state my business.

1038
01:06:56,367 --> 01:06:58,661
You can run, so you're able-bodied.

1039
01:06:58,745 --> 01:07:01,247
And judging by your audition,
you seem to be of sound mind.

1040
01:07:01,331 --> 01:07:02,915
Instead of trying to make some shady deal,

1041
01:07:02,999 --> 01:07:05,418
why don't you try doing
some actual work for a change?

1042
01:07:06,377 --> 01:07:08,463
<i>It is like talking to a brick wall.</i>

1043
01:07:08,546 --> 01:07:11,215
You should get lost now. Let's go.

1044
01:07:11,299 --> 01:07:13,593
Hey! Hold on.

1045
01:07:23,936 --> 01:07:25,104
<i>Wait.</i>

1046
01:07:25,772 --> 01:07:28,191
<i>Where is this murderous aura coming from?</i>

1047
01:07:40,453 --> 01:07:41,663
Hold on!

1048
01:07:42,330 --> 01:07:44,749
Stop. You must not get in that palanquin.

1049
01:07:44,832 --> 01:07:46,918
If you don't stop,
I will report you for stalking.

1050
01:07:47,001 --> 01:07:48,795
I just sensed an assassin's presence.

1051
01:07:48,878 --> 01:07:51,381
Someone nearby is after your life!
Get down!

1052
01:07:51,464 --> 01:07:53,883
This woman is unbelievable.
Get her away from me.

1053
01:07:53,966 --> 01:07:56,010
Miss, that's enough.
Do you have any idea who this is?

1054
01:07:56,094 --> 01:07:58,388
You scoundrels! Unhand me at once!

1055
01:07:59,013 --> 01:08:00,014
You cannot!

1056
01:08:00,098 --> 01:08:01,224
I told you to get down!

1057
01:08:01,307 --> 01:08:04,394
You scoundrels must search the vicinity!

1058
01:08:04,477 --> 01:08:05,561
Damn it.

1059
01:08:06,229 --> 01:08:07,146
Wait.

1060
01:09:42,368 --> 01:09:45,953
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1061
01:10:16,067 --> 01:10:18,110
<i>I am the one who saved your life.</i>

1062
01:10:18,194 --> 01:10:20,071
<i>You dare forsake your savior?</i>

1063
01:10:20,905 --> 01:10:22,615
<i>Find out everything you can about her.</i>

1064
01:10:22,698 --> 01:10:23,783
<i>In this place,</i>

1065
01:10:23,866 --> 01:10:26,244
<i>it seems even breathing</i>
<i>causes money to drain away.</i>

1066
01:10:26,327 --> 01:10:27,912
<i>You don't think</i>
<i>someone put her up to this?</i>

1067
01:10:27,995 --> 01:10:30,081
<i>There's no shortage of people</i>
<i>who want to see me crash and burn.</i>

1068
01:10:30,164 --> 01:10:31,082
Welcome, Se-gye.

1069
01:10:31,165 --> 01:10:33,042
Poor educational background,
a tragic family history…

1070
01:10:33,251 --> 01:10:34,418
<i>It all makes sense now.</i>

1071
01:10:34,502 --> 01:10:37,171
<i>In this life,</i>
<i>I will do what I must to survive it.</i>

1072
01:10:37,255 --> 01:10:38,798
<i>Are you going to get paid?</i>

1073
01:10:38,881 --> 01:10:39,841
<i>We're sold out!</i>

1074
01:10:39,924 --> 01:10:41,801
<i>-It's sold out!</i>
<i>-Sold out!</i>

1075
01:10:41,884 --> 01:10:43,094
Found you.

1076
01:10:43,761 --> 01:10:44,929
<i>Shin Seo-ri.</i>

1077
01:10:50,270 --> 01:10:52,270
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim

